The paper deals with algorithms and data structures for searching a bitstream, which is a classic problem in computer science. The use of a sparse matrix and a constrained walk suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The practical relevance to cryptography and bioinformatics suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The use of ratio of ones to zeroes suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Finally, the linear time algorithm suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
